Class AbstractQueue<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • abstracts.AbstractQueue<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HasInvariant, UnboundedStorageSpecification<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Queue2Stack, QueueShareStack

    public abstract class AbstractQueue<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements HasInvariant, UnboundedStorageSpecification<T>
    This class is an abstraction of UnboundedStorageSpecification
    It implements all basic methods of a queue
    As project's requirement, the queue is built by 2 stacks.
    The testing instance of both stacks may be UnreliableStack or ReliableStack
    Author:
    btdiem
